1
00:00:23,456 --> 00:00:26,793
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>The Amazon Trio found out</i>
<i>they're not really human.</i>

2
00:00:26,827 --> 00:00:31,364
<i>And without Pegasus's horn,</i>
<i>the magic spell that makes them</i>
<i>appear human will wear off.</i>

3
00:00:31,431 --> 00:00:34,801
<i>Also, Fish's Eye fell</i>
<i>in love with Mamo...</i>

4
00:00:34,835 --> 00:00:36,637
<i>But you can't have him!</i>

5
00:00:36,670 --> 00:00:39,005
<i>Mamo's the most handsome</i>
<i>man in the whole world!</i>

6
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,541
‐So hands off!
‐So hands off!

7
00:00:49,616 --> 00:00:59,660
♪

8
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:19,686
♪

9
00:01:19,686 --> 00:01:39,706
♪

10
00:01:39,706 --> 00:01:59,726
♪

11
00:01:59,726 --> 00:02:10,544
♪

12
00:02:17,216 --> 00:02:22,155
<i>[rainfall]</i>

13
00:02:23,489 --> 00:02:24,324
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>What's wrong?</i>

14
00:02:27,794 --> 00:02:31,965
Come on, now. You won't be much
of a love rival looking like
that.

15
00:02:43,677 --> 00:02:48,281
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>"Mirrors of Dreams: The</i>
<i>Amazons' Last Stage"</i>

16
00:02:59,025 --> 00:03:01,668
You feeling any better?

17
00:03:09,275 --> 00:03:12,378
Here. Your hair's
still dripping wet.

18
00:03:16,717 --> 00:03:21,054
You're not from around
here, are you?

19
00:03:21,121 --> 00:03:23,123
<i>What school do you go to?</i>

20
00:03:24,858 --> 00:03:28,194
You're someone who possesses
a lot of dreams, I'm told.

21
00:03:28,228 --> 00:03:29,029
[gasp]

22
00:03:29,062 --> 00:03:32,032
That's how Mamo thinks
of you, anyway.

23
00:03:32,065 --> 00:03:35,168
[grunt] You mean you
saw him again?!..

24
00:03:35,201 --> 00:03:37,370
Where!? When!?

25
00:03:37,403 --> 00:03:41,374
Is that what your sitting out
there in the rain was all about?

26
00:03:41,374 --> 00:03:43,810
Did that have something
to do with Mamo!?

27
00:03:43,844 --> 00:03:48,414
Y'know, these awkward silences
aren't very helpful.

28
00:03:48,481 --> 00:03:52,085
You're always so
happy‐go‐lucky...

29
00:03:52,152 --> 00:03:54,187
[small grunt]

30
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:59,159
I really envy you. To be so
full of dreams like that...

31
00:03:59,192 --> 00:04:01,027
(Zirconia)
Now do you understand!?

32
00:04:01,061 --> 00:04:07,173
You are not human... I merely
used magic to give you a human
form.

33
00:04:07,207 --> 00:04:09,342
I see.

34
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:12,245
And that's why we don't
have beautiful dreams?

35
00:04:12,245 --> 00:04:17,350
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Here, have some tea...</i>
<i>It'll warm you up.</i>

36
00:04:20,086 --> 00:04:23,123
what's your greatest,
fondest dream?

37
00:04:23,189 --> 00:04:25,291
[groan] come on!

38
00:04:25,358 --> 00:04:30,096
You're s'posed to be my rival,
can't you even guess what it
is?...

39
00:04:30,096 --> 00:04:31,097
[gasp]

40
00:04:35,068 --> 00:04:39,405
I see... Yes, of course...

41
00:04:39,438 --> 00:04:43,076
I should have known that would
be your most beautiful dream.

42
00:04:47,447 --> 00:04:48,949
[gasp]

43
00:04:50,617 --> 00:04:54,955
Tell me something, is that the
smile Mamo gets on his face
when he's alone with you?

44
00:04:54,988 --> 00:04:59,593
Listen, would you mind not
calling him "Mamo" like
you've known him forever?

45
00:04:59,626 --> 00:05:04,304
In fact, let me makes this
clear, I want you to stop
making moves on him.

46
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:09,910
Of course, he is the best
looking man in the world, so I
give you points for good taste.

47
00:05:09,943 --> 00:05:11,578
[gasp]

48
00:05:11,612 --> 00:05:14,981
But you've attacked the
best‐looking of them all, which
means you've got good taste.

49
00:05:15,015 --> 00:05:17,283
Way | good for your own good!

50
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:21,822
<i>[stunned gasp]... Could this</i>
<i>girl...be Sailor Moon?</i>

51
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:26,993
<i>(Ikuko Tsukino)</i>
<i>Usagi? I need you to</i>
<i>run an errand for me.</i>

52
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:29,029
Yeah, all right!

53
00:05:29,095 --> 00:05:33,166
Wait for me here, okay?
I'll be right back.

54
00:05:33,266 --> 00:05:37,003
And then you and I will settle
our Mamo issues once and for
all.

55
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:52,853
Sailor Moon...

56
00:05:52,886 --> 00:05:57,223
What's so great about her?
Why do you like <i>her?</i>

57
00:05:57,290 --> 00:06:00,634
She's full of
dreams, that's why.

58
00:06:01,535 --> 00:06:03,403
[gasp]

59
00:06:05,506 --> 00:06:08,542
<i>Is that what makes</i>
<i>her so strong?</i>

60
00:06:15,248 --> 00:06:17,518
[curious gasp]

61
00:06:18,418 --> 00:06:20,887
<i>(Chibi Usa)</i>
<i>Pegasus. Please come out.</i>

62
00:06:21,221 --> 00:06:22,989
<i>(Pegasus)</i>
<i>You called?</i>

63
00:06:23,023 --> 00:06:24,991
[shocked gasp]

64
00:06:30,564 --> 00:06:31,397
[gasp]

65
00:06:31,464 --> 00:06:34,568
There's something
I don't understand.

66
00:06:34,601 --> 00:06:35,569
What's that?

67
00:06:35,602 --> 00:06:39,439
<i>Pegasus! So that little</i>
<i>girl is the host??</i>

68
00:06:40,006 --> 00:06:43,276
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>To catch Pegasus, you must</i>
<i>first capture his host.</i>

69
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:51,585
There is only one way for you to
keep the human forms that you
currently have.

70
00:06:51,585 --> 00:06:53,253
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>Find Pegasus.</i>

71
00:06:53,353 --> 00:06:58,124
<i>Only by using the power of that</i>
<i>horn on his head known as the</i>
<i>Golden Crystal ...</i>

72
00:06:58,191 --> 00:07:01,034
<i>...will you be able to</i>
<i>remain as you are.</i>

73
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:05,271
Ohh. I get it now.

74
00:07:05,305 --> 00:07:08,408
Mom, I'm back!

75
00:07:08,441 --> 00:07:11,945
But‐‐ Wait, where's Chibi‐Usa,
wasn't she with you?

76
00:07:11,978 --> 00:07:13,446
Hm?

77
00:07:13,479 --> 00:07:17,150
I thought she was in the house
but she's not. Where could she
have gone?

78
00:07:17,217 --> 00:07:19,653
She's probably just out playing
with her friends somewhere.

79
00:07:22,589 --> 00:07:24,991
<i>[rainfall]</i>

80
00:07:25,325 --> 00:07:29,095
What?! You have found
the host of Pegasus?

81
00:07:29,129 --> 00:07:30,731
Who is it?

82
00:07:32,666 --> 00:07:36,570
What's wrong? Speak up!

83
00:07:36,603 --> 00:07:41,141
Well, first, I have one
question, Madame Zirconia.

84
00:07:41,141 --> 00:07:42,342
[groan]

85
00:07:42,408 --> 00:07:47,413
Can we ever become human?
I mean, truly human?

86
00:07:47,447 --> 00:07:50,684
What are you talking about?

87
00:07:50,751 --> 00:07:53,754
Even if we're able to keep these
human forms you've given us...

88
00:07:53,787 --> 00:07:59,192
...without the ability to dream
beautiful dreams, then we're
human in appearance and nothing
more.

89
00:07:59,259 --> 00:08:02,135
So can we ever really call
ourselves "human?"

90
00:08:04,838 --> 00:08:08,509
Madame Zirconia!
Please answer me!

91
00:08:13,179 --> 00:08:24,357
[agonized screams]

92
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:26,627
Please, make it stop,
Madame Zirconia!

93
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:28,795
[grunt]

94
00:08:28,829 --> 00:08:30,731
[gasp]

95
00:08:30,797 --> 00:08:34,367
Expendable pawns should
mind their place!

96
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,869
[annoyed grunt]

97
00:08:35,902 --> 00:08:41,808
Remember that, in reality,
you're only a bunch of
animals, so don't get cocky.

98
00:08:45,478 --> 00:08:48,549
Well. I don't need you to find
out what I want to know.

99
00:08:48,549 --> 00:08:50,350
Right, Zircon?

100
00:08:59,259 --> 00:09:03,403
<i>(Zirconia)</i>
<i>So... That's the girl who</i>
<i>is host to Pegasus, eh?</i>

101
00:09:03,436 --> 00:09:07,741
No, you're mistaken! That one
has nothing to do with it!

102
00:09:08,609 --> 00:09:10,877
Hawk's Eye, you will go.

103
00:09:10,911 --> 00:09:12,245
As you wish.

104
00:09:12,245 --> 00:09:18,552
This is the magic orb that
changed the three of you
into human form...

105
00:09:18,585 --> 00:09:22,455
This same orb can also grant
you your wish, but only once.

106
00:09:22,523 --> 00:09:28,094
So, if you can capture
Pegasus and fuel the orb
with the power of his horn,

107
00:09:28,128 --> 00:09:32,465
the Golden Crystal, you
will be able to remain
in human form forever.

108
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:35,536
Hm!

109
00:09:35,569 --> 00:09:37,437
Hawk's Eye!

110
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:44,210
Tiger's Eye, you will keep
an eye on Fish's Eye.

111
00:09:44,244 --> 00:09:46,379
Yes.

112
00:09:46,747 --> 00:09:49,449
It's all right. I can
manage by myself.

113
00:09:49,482 --> 00:09:51,618
[gasp]

114
00:09:52,753 --> 00:09:54,621
Here, hang onto me.

115
00:09:54,655 --> 00:09:57,390
[grunt] What are you doing!?

116
00:09:58,424 --> 00:10:00,567
<i>Fish's Eye! Come back!</i>

117
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:07,073
Hm! I think this might
be the end of the road
for the Amazon Trio.

118
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:11,845
<i>[playful giggling]</i>

119
00:10:11,878 --> 00:10:15,348
Go ahead. Do what
you want with them.

120
00:10:15,381 --> 00:10:25,091
[playful laughter]

121
00:10:33,266 --> 00:10:38,705
[playful laughter]

122
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:46,813
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

123
00:10:52,385 --> 00:11:01,301
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

124
00:11:04,470 --> 00:11:07,574
(Makoto)
I'm getting worried. It's not
like her to stay out this late.

125
00:11:07,608 --> 00:11:10,476
Yeah...

126
00:11:14,447 --> 00:11:18,919
<i>[rainfall]</i>

127
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,188
<i>(Thinking)</i>
<i>Where could she have gone?</i>

128
00:11:22,255 --> 00:11:24,591
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>Does Chibi‐Usa</i>
<i>come here a lot?</i>

129
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:26,492
Huh?

130
00:11:26,527 --> 00:11:29,963
Oh, Chibi‐Usa? No, I doubt
it. Not as far as I know.

131
00:11:29,996 --> 00:11:32,599
Huh?? Then what're
we doing here?

132
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:35,702
What's going on? Who were you
expecting to find here, anyway??

133
00:11:35,769 --> 00:11:37,270
[gasp]

134
00:11:37,303 --> 00:11:38,805
Usagi!

135
00:11:38,839 --> 00:11:40,541
Pull yourself
together, would you?

136
00:11:40,607 --> 00:11:43,844
All right, never mind, let's
split up and keep looking.

137
00:11:52,653 --> 00:11:54,154
I hope I'm not intruding.

138
00:11:54,187 --> 00:11:54,888
Huh?

139
00:11:54,955 --> 00:11:57,157
Sorry, this isn't
really like me.

140
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,358
What?

141
00:11:58,358 --> 00:12:01,034
...matter of fact, you aren't
even remotely my type.

142
00:12:01,067 --> 00:12:02,903
What is with this guy??

143
00:12:02,969 --> 00:12:04,871
<i>[snap]</i>

144
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:08,374
[gasp]

145
00:12:08,842 --> 00:12:09,643
One...

146
00:12:09,676 --> 00:12:10,711
[gasp]

147
00:12:10,744 --> 00:12:12,679
Two...

148
00:12:12,713 --> 00:12:13,514
[scream]

149
00:12:13,547 --> 00:12:14,848
...and three!

150
00:12:14,881 --> 00:12:19,753
[agonized screams]

151
00:12:22,488 --> 00:12:24,558
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>Stop! She's not the one!</i>

152
00:12:24,558 --> 00:12:25,826
[grunt]

153
00:12:29,896 --> 00:12:33,399
[grunts]
Have you gone nuts, Fish's Eye!?

154
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:36,903
Stop this nonsense, Hawk's
Eye! Let Sailor go right now!

155
00:12:36,937 --> 00:12:38,539
Sailor...

156
00:12:38,572 --> 00:12:39,740
...Moon??

157
00:12:40,674 --> 00:12:44,210
You're saying this
girl is Sailor Moon?

158
00:12:44,244 --> 00:12:47,080
Then all the more reason to
check her dreams out...

159
00:12:47,113 --> 00:12:49,516
<i>(crazed laughter)</i>

160
00:12:54,588 --> 00:12:59,560
Uhh...

161
00:12:59,593 --> 00:13:01,902
Allow me to introduce myself.

162
00:13:01,935 --> 00:13:04,605
I am Mister Magic Pierrot.

163
00:13:04,605 --> 00:13:07,107
Mister Magic Pierrot?

164
00:13:07,140 --> 00:13:11,244
[crazed laughter]

165
00:13:11,277 --> 00:13:13,213
Argh!

166
00:13:14,047 --> 00:13:19,219
[screaming]

167
00:13:19,252 --> 00:13:21,221
Ooh! Wow! Amazing!

168
00:13:21,254 --> 00:13:23,890
But no Pegasus, I'm afraid.

169
00:13:23,924 --> 00:13:25,792
Who the blazes
are you, anyway?!

170
00:13:25,792 --> 00:13:29,129
I'm on an errand for
Madame Zirconia.

171
00:13:29,129 --> 00:13:32,232
She sent me to take
out the garbage.

172
00:13:32,265 --> 00:13:34,267
The garbage?

173
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,670
That's right, the garbage.

174
00:13:36,737 --> 00:13:39,806
Now, keep your eyes
right on me...

175
00:13:39,806 --> 00:13:42,809
That's right... Watch
the birdie...

176
00:13:42,843 --> 00:13:44,945
Voilà!

177
00:13:45,979 --> 00:13:47,781
[gasps]

178
00:13:48,682 --> 00:13:50,283
Hey! What are you doing!?

179
00:13:50,316 --> 00:13:54,287
Who, me? Like I said, I'm taking
out the garbage, garbage ...
Hyah!

180
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,488
[grunt]

181
00:13:55,856 --> 00:13:56,823
[grunts]

182
00:13:57,691 --> 00:13:59,660
[painful screams]

183
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:02,168
[horrified gasp]

184
00:14:10,176 --> 00:14:13,714
All of her... beautiful
dreams...

185
00:14:13,780 --> 00:14:17,117
Come on! You're s'posed
to be my rival,

186
00:14:17,150 --> 00:14:19,219
can't you even guess what it is?

187
00:14:19,285 --> 00:14:20,687
[giggle]

188
00:14:30,196 --> 00:14:34,000
[sob]

189
00:14:34,034 --> 00:14:35,869
Let's try that again!

190
00:14:36,870 --> 00:14:38,539
[gasp]

191
00:14:42,008 --> 00:14:45,679
[gasps]

192
00:14:46,346 --> 00:14:48,314
[groan]

193
00:14:48,348 --> 00:14:51,752
One sack of garbage
down, two to go!

194
00:14:51,818 --> 00:14:55,055
[grunt] Try this...!

195
00:14:56,389 --> 00:14:58,258
Why, sure!

196
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:02,603
Thanks!

197
00:15:03,904 --> 00:15:06,039
[weak groan]

198
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,173
Hawk's Eye!

199
00:15:07,207 --> 00:15:08,842
Hawk's Eye!

200
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,744
Why did you do that!?

201
00:15:10,744 --> 00:15:13,914
Like she said, we're
expendable...

202
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:20,353
I thought if I captured Pegasus,
then the three of us could
become human and prove her wrong

203
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:25,391
...Prove that the Amazon Trio
was more than just a joke.

204
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:27,861
Hawk's Eye!

205
00:15:27,894 --> 00:15:28,862
Don't give up!

206
00:15:28,895 --> 00:15:32,065
[painful grunt]

207
00:15:32,866 --> 00:15:34,768
...take it...

208
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:38,138
[gasp]

209
00:15:40,306 --> 00:15:44,077
Hawk's Eye!!

210
00:15:45,111 --> 00:15:48,048
[laughing]

211
00:15:48,081 --> 00:15:50,150
You dare!

212
00:15:50,216 --> 00:15:52,619
[scream]

213
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:57,791
For my next trick... [chuckle]

214
00:15:57,791 --> 00:15:58,759
[shocked gasp]

215
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:01,301
[loud grunt]

216
00:16:02,268 --> 00:16:04,070
Huh?

217
00:16:08,174 --> 00:16:09,109
[hiss]

218
00:16:09,142 --> 00:16:10,811
[scream]

219
00:16:10,811 --> 00:16:16,016
That's it? That's the best that
the Amazon Trio, the "stars" of
the Dead Moon, can do?

220
00:16:16,082 --> 00:16:18,652
[crazed laughter]

221
00:16:18,685 --> 00:16:21,254
This clown is strong... Ideas?

222
00:16:26,292 --> 00:16:27,360
Tiger's Eye...

223
00:16:27,427 --> 00:16:28,595
Yeah?

224
00:16:28,629 --> 00:16:31,364
Listen, I actually do
know where Pegasus is hiding.

225
00:16:31,431 --> 00:16:32,766
I found his host.

226
00:16:32,799 --> 00:16:34,601
Hm?

227
00:16:34,635 --> 00:16:40,306
So we could use this magic orb's
power and make ourselves human
forever...But even then,

228
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:45,178
we'd still most likely lose the
battle and then we'll have died
without avenging Hawk's Eye...

229
00:16:45,211 --> 00:16:50,183
That's why I'm asking you to let
me use it for something else...

230
00:16:54,354 --> 00:16:59,159
You really think Sailor Moon has
a chance of defeating that guy?

231
00:16:59,192 --> 00:17:02,969
<i>(Fish's Eye)</i>
<i>I know she can.</i>

232
00:17:03,003 --> 00:17:05,872
Alright.

233
00:17:05,872 --> 00:17:10,176
If the Amazon Trio's got
to go out, at least we
can go out with a bang.

234
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:13,179
Tiger's Eye...

235
00:17:13,246 --> 00:17:18,752
If we're ever reborn, let's
make sure we all come back
as humans.

236
00:17:18,819 --> 00:17:21,522
Have you two finished
saying your farewells?

237
00:17:21,555 --> 00:17:23,023
‐Not yet!
‐Not yet!

238
00:17:30,564 --> 00:17:32,398
What the heck are you doing?

239
00:17:32,398 --> 00:17:35,902
We ask you grant us
our last wish...!

240
00:17:39,405 --> 00:17:41,374
[gasp]

241
00:17:52,052 --> 00:17:53,920
Usagi!

242
00:17:53,954 --> 00:17:55,522
Chibi‐Usa!

243
00:17:56,590 --> 00:17:58,925
